        -:   33:/*!
        -:   34:  \class SoFaceSet SoFaceSet.h Inventor/nodes/SoFaceSet.h
        -:   35:  \brief The SoFaceSet class is used to render and organize non-indexed polygonal face data.
        -:   36:
        -:   37:  \ingroup coin_nodes
        -:   38:
        -:   39:  Facesets are specified using the numVertices field. Coordinates,
        -:   40:  normals, materials and texture coordinates are fetched in order from
        -:   41:  the current state or from the vertexProperty node if set. For
        -:   42:  example, if numVertices is set to [3, 4, 5, 3], this node would
        -:   43:  specify a triangle from coordinates 0, 1 and 2, a quad from
        -:   44:  coordinates 3, 4, 5 and 6, a polygon from coordinates 7, 8, 9, 10
        -:   45:  and 11 and finally a triangle from coordinates 12, 13, 14.
        -:   46:
        -:   47:  Binding PER_VERTEX, PER_FACE or OVERALL can be set for material,
        -:   48:  and normals. The default material binding is OVERALL. The default
        -:   49:  normal binding is PER_VERTEX.
        -:   50:
        -:   51:  For more elaborate documentation about face sets, see the class
        -:   52:  documentation of the SoIndexedFaceSet node, which contains examples
        -:   53:  and more detailed information about various issues also relevant for
        -:   54:  this node.
        -:   55:
        -:   56:  <b>FILE FORMAT/DEFAULTS:</b>
        -:   57:  \code
        -:   58:    FaceSet {
        -:   59:        vertexProperty NULL
        -:   60:        startIndex 0
        -:   61:        numVertices -1
        -:   62:    }
        -:   63:  \endcode
        -:   64:
        -:   65:  \sa SoIndexedFaceSet, SoIndexedTriangleStripSet
